{"word":"προσοιστέος","slug":"προσοιστέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>προσοιστέος</b></el> <el>(προς-οιστέος, η, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:προσφέρω'><el>προσφέρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be added to</i>, <el>τινί</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>προσοιστέον</el> <i>one must add</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>one must apply, use</i>, <el>γυμνάσια</el> <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}